    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.68,
      "end": 5.56,
      "text": "This is a Levi-Vox recording. All Levi-Vox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.76,
      "end": 11.42,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LeviVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 13.22,
      "end": 16.12,
      "text": "Asop's fables. The farmer and the fox.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 17.86,
      "end": 23.74,
      "text": "A farmer was greatly annoyed by a fox, which came prowling about his yard at night and carried off his pals.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 23.74,
      "end": 26.78,
      "text": "So he set the trap for him and caught him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 27.52,
      "end": 33.46,
      "text": "And in order to be revengeed upon him, he tied a bunch of toe to his tail and set fire to it and let him go.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 34.76,
      "end": 41.08,
      "text": "As elok would have it however, the fox made straight for the fields where the corn was standing ripe and ready for cutting.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 41.7,
      "end": 46.74,
      "text": "He quickly caught fire and was all burnt up and the farmer lost all his harvest.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 49.28,
      "end": 51.08,
      "text": "Revenge is a two-edged sword.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 53.54,
      "end": 55.12,
      "text": "End of the farmer and the fox.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
